<title>SINGAPORE: Shangri-la 1996 net profit down 7 pct.</title>
<headline>Shangri-la 1996 net profit down 7 pct.</headline>
<dateline>SINGAPORE 1997-03-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year to December 31,1996</p>
<p>		   (in millions of S$ unless stated)</p>
<p>    Net profit			     19.80 vs   21.35</p>
<p>    Dividend (cents)			7.00   vs    7.00</p>
<p>    Group share (cents)		  11.96   vs   12.94</p>
<p>    Group share fully diluted	  12.05   vs   13.04</p>
<p>    Turnover				137.20   vs  135.43</p>
<p>    Investment income		    11.16   vs   12.78</p>
<p>    Other income incl. interest	 0.01   vs    0.02</p>
<p>    Interest (expense)		    7.59   vs    6.27</p>
<p>    Depreciation/amortisation	   9.25   vs    9.29</p>
<p>    Pre-tax profit			 30.25   vs   32.98</p>
<p>    Income from associates		2.92   vs    4.57</p>
<p>    Tax					 7.27   vs    6.88</p>
<p>    Minorities (losses)		   0.26   vs    0.08</p>
<p>    Extraordinaries (gains)	    46.26   vs   40.15</p>
<p>    Dividend payment date		 June 20, 1997</p>
<p>    Books closing date		    June 9, 1997</p>
<p>Note - Shangri-la Hotel Ltd is a hotel operator.</p>
<p>-- Singapore newsroom (65 870 3199)</p>
